    "We set r = 128 for LoRA, n = 6000 for FourierFT, and n = 4500 for MaCP, with tuned learning rates and weight decay, training for 7 epochs.",
    "Results and Analysis.",
    "Table 7 presents the multitask evaluation results for video-text tasks using the VL-BART backbone.",
    "MaCP achieves top or near-top performance across all tasks while using significantly fewer trainable parameters.",
    "For TVQA and YC2C, MaCP matches the highest scores of 76.3 and 154, respectively, while reducing parameters by over 99% compared to full fine-tuning."
